{"title": "Unsanitized user input in OS command", "summary": " Using external or user-defined input directly in an OS command can allow attackers to perform dangerous commands on the operating system. ", "description": "\nUsing external or user-defined input directly in an OS command can allow attackers to perform dangerous commands on the operating system.\n", "recommendations": "\n\nThink twice if user input is really needed there.\n\nIt might be possible to use dynamic hardcoded values:\n\n```javascript\n  let filePattern = \"*.js\"\n\n  if req.params.graphql {\n    filePattern = \"*.gql\"\n  }\n\n  cp.exec(`cp ${filePattern} foo`, (error, stdout, stderr) => {});\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-78"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/javascript_lang_os_command_injection", "https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/Command_Injection"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}